## Summary
This documentation explains sample ratio mismatch (SRM) in Amplitude Experiment, where observed variant allocations significantly differ from specified allocations, potentially indicating data biases that can invalidate experiment results, and outlines common causes including instrumentation errors, mid-experiment configuration changes, and variant jumping.

